    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "DG",
    "text": "This is a picture of my father, Lazar Zeigerson And it was taken before the war, maybe 1936, '35, '36. It was in a resort place. The name of the place was [? Krosniewice ?] in Poland. [PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] This is a family picture. It was taken about 1930. And this is my father, Lazar Zeigerson, my mother, Syma Zeigerson my brother, Sidney, my sister Leah, and me, Dorothy Grinims. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] The photo on the right, on the extreme right, that's the-- the mother Stepaniuk and the son, Lusik Stepaniuk. That's the policeman that saved my life, our lives, my husband's, too. And on-- on the extreme left, that's a cousin. [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the picture on the left, that's my mother with my oldest brother. [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The picture on the extreme right is when I was approximately 12, 13 years old",
